  "source_file": "zymo-quick-custom.ot2.apiv2.py",
  "intent_precise": "Zymo Quick-DNA/RNA Viral Kit with PCR Prep: Using magplate (deep_well_plate, slot 3), flatplate (pcr_plate, slot 3), Liquid Waste (reservoir, slot 11), Opentrons 24 TubeRack (tuberack, slot 8). With magnetic module. (1) Transfer from source to destination. (2) Transfer from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (3) Transfer from source to destination. (4) Pause: Replace 20 ul tip rack on slot 5 (5) Pause: Replace all 200 ul tip racks on Slots 3, 6, and 9 (6) Transfer 4\u00b5L from source to destination. (7) Mix 5 times at 200\u00b5L. (8) Transfer 160\u00b5L from source to destination. (9) Transfer 160\u00b5L from source to destination. (10) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (11) Incubate for 5 minutes. (12) Transfer 180\u00b5L from source to destination. (13) Transfer from source to destination. (14) Disengage magnets to release beads. (15) Transfer 165\u00b5L from source to destination. (16) Transfer 165\u00b5L from source to destination. (17) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (18) Incubate for 3 minutes. (19) Disengage magnets to release beads. (20) Incubate for 2 minutes. (21) Transfer 180\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (22) Incubate for 10 minutes. (23) Disengage magnets to release beads. (24) Transfer 60\u00b5L from source to destination. (25) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (26) Incubate for 10 minutes. (27) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (28) Incubate for 2 minutes. (29) Transfer 20\u00b5L from source to destination. (30) Transfer 5\u00b5L from source to destination. (31) Mix 5 times at 20\u00b5L. (32) Disengage magnets to release beads.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation. (volumes 4\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~35 min total)",
  "intent": "For this Zymo Quick-DNA/RNA Viral Kit protocol, you'll be working with the magnetic module using the deep well plate in slot 3, PCR plate also in slot 3, liquid waste reservoir in slot 11, and the 24-tube rack in slot 8. Start by performing the initial transfers, then pause to replace the 20\u00b5L tip rack on slot 5 and all 200\u00b5L tip racks on slots 3, 6, and 9. The key steps involve transferring 4\u00b5L to your samples, mixing 5 times at 200\u00b5L, then doing 160\u00b5L transfers before engaging the magnets at the specified height for 5-minute bead separation, followed by 180\u00b5L supernatant removal. Continue with wash steps using 165\u00b5L transfers, magnetic separations of 3 minutes, then proceed to the elution phase with specific transfers from A1 to A1, 10-minute incubations, and final transfers of 60\u00b5L, 50\u00b5L, 20\u00b5L, and 5\u00b5L with mixing 5 times at 20\u00b5L volume before releasing the beads.",
